<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF32FF6BFF43F9AE8829F93C" blockId="135.[151,1436,1557,1823]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="ED9D3623FF32FF6BFF43F9AE8AB0F98C" bold="true" box="[199,479,1637,1663]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The superior volsella is small and differs from most species by having a broad and low base bearing 3 inner setae and a slightly curved projection bearing 1 lateral seta. The gonostylus is relatively stout, widest at about middle, with pointed apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF56EA31FF32FF6BFF43F9168A31F904" blockId="135.[151,1436,1557,1823]" box="[199,350,1757,1783]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
